{
  "doc_id": "12267",
  "text": "Our findings have particular relevance to AD because it is established that AD patients display elevated circulating cortisol levels [CITATION_1] . Clinical data also suggest that a stressful lifestyle, which would result in elevated cortisol levels can be a risk factor for AD onset [CITATION_2] . In addition, another strong risk factor for AD is the presence of the apoE4 allele, which has been shown to elevate CSF cortisol levels [CITATION_3] more so than the E3 or the E2 allele.",
  "correct_citation": {
